title: Dungeon Born
author: Dakota Krout
description: Cal, a hapless dungeon dweller, stumbles into his latest adventure when a threat materializes out of the shadows, threatening to crush him beneath its unyielding malice. With his survival and fledgling powers hanging in the balance, Cal must navigate the treacherous path to growth and revenge. Dungeon Core.

title: Defiance of the Fall
author: TheFirstDefier
description: Zac's world ended the moment he was left alone in the wilderness, a tiny speck of dust amidst an unforgiving multiverse teeming with deadly beasts and demons. With his family's fate hanging by a thread as the cosmos itself began to unravel, he steeled himself for a desperate fight to survive - Cultivation / System Apocalypse.

title: Beware of Chicken: A Xianxia Cultivation Novel
author: Casualfarmer
description:
A lone figure emerges from the shadows, driven by an insatiable hunger for power that will reshape the very fabric of reality. As they embark on a perilous journey to claim their destiny, the fate of worlds hangs in the balance.

Progression Fantasy.

title: Time to Play
author: Erin Ampersand
description:
Meghan Moretti's life went from bad to worse when reality TV stars turned evil space rodents invaded Earth, forcing her to hide her kids from monstrous contestants and navigate the treacherous game for their survival. As the stakes rise, Meghan must confront the horrific truth: her own children will be forced to fight in this nightmarish game too.

System Apocalypse.

title: Forge of Destiny
author: Yrsillar
description: As the last embers of sunlight fade, a lone figure emerges from the shadows, driven by an ancient power that courses through their veins like liquid fire. Their quest to reclaim a lost world will reshape the very fabric of existence, or succumb to the crushing weight of its own destiny. Progression Fantasy.

title: All the Skills: A Deck-Building LitRPG
author: Honour Rae
description:
In a world where the Baron's dark power hangs in the balance, Arthur flees Border Village #49 to escape his tyrant ruler and reclaim his stolen heart card, hoping to build on its legendary potential. With his life and fate forever tied to the card's secrets, Arthur sets out to forge new skills and master its ancient magic.

Progression Fantasy.

title: The Land: Founding: A LitRPG Saga
author: Aleron Kong
description:
Richter, a former outcast, was forced to flee after his own magic turned against him in The Land of banished gods and monsters. Now, he's driven by a singular goal: forging his own kingdom and shaping the future of this unforgiving world - at any cost.

GameLit.

title: The Primal Hunter
author: Zogarth
description:
Here's a 2-sentence book blurb that meets the rules:

Jake, a bored office worker with no idea what hit him, finds himself dropped into a vast multiverse where monsters roam and power hangs in the balance. Now, he must level up, slay beasts, and collect loot to become the ultimate apex hunter before his new world succumbs to chaos - GameLit / Isekai / Progression Fantasy.

title: Life Reset
author: Shemer Kuznits
description: Oren, a former digital prodigy reduced to a pitiful goblin form in the virtual realm of NEO, was forced to watch his friends ascend to mighty beasts while he was stuck in this lowly body. To escape the cycle of servitude and reclaim his lost powers, Oren must participate in the grim tournament – Monster Evolution.

title: Kairos: The Last Gods
author: Maxime J. Durand
description:
In a world ravaged by floods and the crumbling remains of Mount Olympus, Kairos emerges from obscurity to claim his rightful place as the newest deity, driven by an insatiable hunger for power. With monsters at his feet and conquests to be won, he sets out to reshape the shattered realm in his image.

GameLit / Dungeon Crawl / Isekai.

title: Awaken Online: Catharsis
author: Travis Bagwell
description: As Jason logs into Awaken Online, the last thing he expects is to be pushed down a path of darkness and discovery, where he's forced to confront the possibility that he might be the villain in this virtual world. With no memory of his past or true intentions, Jason must navigate the unknown to uncover his purpose. VR Game.

title: Dungeon Crawler Carl
author: Matt Dinniman
description: When aliens acquire Earth and collapse the surface, Carl and his ex-girlfriend's cat Princess Donut are among the few survivors forced into a deadly dungeon crawl broadcast as entertainment across the galaxy. Armed with nothing but a bathrobe and a surprisingly murderous cat, Carl must descend floor by floor through increasingly absurd horrors while the universe watches and cheers.

title: Shadeslinger
author: Kyle Kirrin
description: Ned Altimer, a low-level warrior in the VRMMO game Earthblood Online, had grown accustomed to his axe's steady weight at his side – until the three-day Head Start period ended and every player with a sword pointed at him. Now he just wants to make it out of this virtual nightmare alive, one pixelated kill at a time. GameLit.

title: Chrysalis: The Antventure Begins
author: RinoZ
description: Anthony, a former adventurer reborn as an ant in the perilous Dungeon of Pangera, must navigate treacherous terrain and cunning foes to build his new home and reclaim his destiny. As his colony grows in strength, so do the stakes for Anthony's very existence - GameLit.

title: Barrow King: An Epic LitRPG/GameLit Adventure
author: C.M. Carney
description:
Finn Caldwell's life was a mess, but nothing could have prepared him for the frantic message from his estranged sister, yanking him into The Realms - a world of holographic reality games where death was just a respawn. To escape, he must defeat the Barrow King and save her from certain doom.

GameLit.

title: One More Last Time
author: Eric Ugland
description: Montana's life was a dumpster fire, but that's when his last friend showed up at the literal last second with an offer to join a mysterious game - because who needs human connection when you've got a chance to win it all? To salvage what's left of his ruined existence, Montana must play by their rules. GameLit.

title: Paranoid Mage
author: Inadvisably Compelled
description: A lone figure, shrouded in mystery, emerges from the shadows of a world on the cusp of catastrophic change. As they embark on an odyssey to reclaim their place in this fractured realm, the fate of existence hangs precariously in the balance. Progression Fantasy.

title: Curious Beginnings
author: V.A. Lewis
description:
Salvos, a newborn demon, emerges from the abyss into the treacherous landscape of The Netherworld, where demons rule with an iron fist and survival is a daily struggle. With her existence hanging by a thread, Salvos must navigate this hellish realm to escape its clutches and forge a new path beyond.

GameLit / Isekai.

title: Viridian Gate Online: Cataclysm
author: James A. Hunter
description: Trapped in the world of Viridian Gate Online, Jack Mitchell found himself lucky enough to stumble into a NexGenVR capsule, risking a one-way trip that would either save or condemn him. Now, with his survival hanging by a thread, he must navigate monsters and cutthroat players to uncover the truth behind the game's corrupt developers. GameLit.

title: The Beginning After the End: Publisher's Pack
author: TurtleMe
description:
As the last remnants of her forgotten past began to stir, a young woman emerged from the shadows, forged in the heart of a world on the brink of catastrophic transformation. With every step, the fate of an entire realm hung precariously in the balance, determined by her unyielding quest for dominance.

Progression Fantasy.

title: He Who Fights with Monsters: A LitRPG Adventure
author: Shirtaloon
description:
As the last remnants of light faded, a lone figure emerged from the shadows, forged in the crucible of forgotten lore and driven by an ancient hunger. Their quest for balance would determine the fate of worlds, and the very fabric of reality itself.

Progression Fantasy.

title: Foundations
author: Cale Plamann
description:
Kat Debs, a brilliant hacker with a penchant for self-destruction, is offered an impossible opportunity: infiltrate the Tower of Somnus, a labyrinthine megacorporate stronghold, free from corporate control. In this treacherous game of life and death, Kat's only goal is to take her destiny – or forfeit it forever.

GameLit.

title: Kill Me If You Can
author: cody.bray
description: Having barely survived his first trials with the worst race and no real skills, Alf now faces an even greater challenge as the Union army tightens its grip. With his snarky AI companion guiding him, he must rapidly gather power and allies while navigating schemes and slavery—always three steps behind but finally gaining ground.

title: Mark of the Fool
author: J.M. Clarke
description:
In a world where the very fabric of reality is unraveling, a lone figure emerges, driven by an ancient power that fuels their quest for redemption. With the fate of existence hanging in the balance, this mysterious hero must navigate treacherous landscapes to reclaim their rightful place.

Progression Fantasy.

title: A Thousand Li: The First Step
author: Tao Wong
description:
As Wu Ying stood amidst the ruins of his village, forced conscription by the army's iron fist weighed upon him, threatening to shatter the tranquility of his rural life forever. Now, with a single decision, he must choose between the comforts of home and the unfathomable allure of immortality on his Thousand Li journey.

Cultivation / System Apocalypse / Isekai.

title: System Clerk [Isekai, LitRPG] (BOOK ONE COMPLETE)
author: WilliamGraves
description: Downed by a night of poor decision-making, Joey found himself catapulted into the System Worlds, forced to face gods and monsters without the crutch of his former life. With no classes, skills, or systems left to fall back on, he must improvise – for survival. Solo Leveling.

title: Life in the North
author: Tao Wong
description: As the last ember of a dying world flickers to life, a lone figure emerges from the shadows, forged in the crucible of forgotten lore and ancient power. Their quest to reclaim the lost arts of their realm hangs precariously in the balance, threatening the very fabric of existence - Progression Fantasy.

title: The Wandering Inn
author: pirateaba
description:
Erin Solstice, a former accountant from another world, found herself transported to a fantastical realm where monster attacks are common and pasta is the only currency that matters. To survive in this bizarre new world, she must battle beasts and bumbling adventurers while running her Wandering Inn successfully.
Isekai / GameLit.

title: Legend of the Arch Magus: Publisher's Pack
author: Michael Sisa
description: As the last remnants of his former life slipped away, Arch Magus Kaelin's malevolent reputation crumbled into dust, replaced by an unassuming visage as the second son of Duke Maric. Now, with a new domain to shape and subjects to uplift, he vowed to unleash a revolution of progress upon the medieval kingdom, Isekai / Progression Fantasy.

title: Azarinth Healer: Book One
author: Rhaegar
description:
Waking up in a world that's 90% monster and 10% paperwork, Ilea discovers she's stuck playing this strange game without any clear goals or objectives - except maybe the one where she gets to be the hero who saves the world from certain doom. Now, she's on a quest to find a place full of magic, monsters, and maybe even a decent latte.

Isekai.

title: NPCs
author: Drew Hayes
description: In the sleepy town of Maplebark, four strangers find themselves bound by a desperate pact: their lives hang in the balance as they don masks and masquerade as adventurers to save their home from certain destruction. As the night wears on, the line between reality and farce blurs, and only one escape is possible. GameLit.

title: Through Adversity: A LitRPG Adventure
author: Alexander Wales
description:
Juniper Smith, a world-weary wordsmith, finds himself stuck in a realm where his own scribbled tales have become twisted reality. As he scrambles to stay one step ahead of the absurdities he's created, Juniper must survive long enough to unravel the mystery behind his own imprisonment.

Isekai / GameLit.

title: The Rage of Dragons
author: Evan Winter
description:
Tau, driven by a burning desire for revenge against those who brutally murdered his loved ones, sets out on a bloody quest to become the greatest swordsman in Omehi history, fueled by a singular purpose to exact justice from his enemies. His relentless pursuit will stop at nothing short of annihilation.

GameLit.

title: Dodge Tank
author: Rick Scott
description: Ryan's mom is dying, and the only way to save her is to become one of Crystal Shards Online's most elite players - a Dodge Tank with an unbeatable dodge ability that just dropped into his hands. To pull off the impossible, he must lead the game world to victory and top the rankings, Solo Leveling.

title: Portal to Nova Roma
author: J.R. Mathews
description: As the last ember of hope flickers within them, a lone figure emerges from the shadows, driven by an unyielding resolve to claim their birthright. Their quest will decide the fate of realms, as ancient powers stir and the very fabric of existence hangs in the balance, Progression Fantasy.

title: Sufficiently Advanced Magic
author: Andrew Rowe
description: Corin Cadence, a thrill-seeker with a taste for darkness, has spent five years obsessed with the Serpent Spire's sinister allure. Now, driven by a hunger to reclaim his lost brother, Corin sets out to scale the treacherous tower and meet the enigmatic goddess at its peak, Tower Climb.

title: Level Up or Die!
author: Apollos Thorne
description:
As the last remnants of sunlight fade from the desolate horizon, a lone figure emerges to forge an uncertain destiny. The fate of their world hangs in the balance as they embark on a perilous journey to unravel the ancient secrets that will determine its fate.

Progression Fantasy.

title: Monsters and Legends
author: Ivan Kal
description:
Zach and Ryun, two unlikely outcasts, crash-land into the Infinite Realm, where they'll grow stronger and face their purpose in this new reality. Punishing the monster that razed their world is just the beginning – making it pay will be the ultimate test of their resolve.

System Apocalypse / Isekai.

title: Bastion
author: Phil Tucker
description:
In a realm of eternal dawn, a lone figure emerges from the shadows, driven by an ancient power that courses through their veins like liquid fire. As they embark on a perilous quest to reclaim a lost legacy, the fate of the world hangs in the balance.

Progression Fantasy.

title: Mother of Learning Arc 1
author: nobody103
description:
Zorian Kazinski, a hapless student at Cyoria's magical academy, found himself stuck in an endless loop of murder and rebirth, with each cycle bringing him one step closer to unraveling the dark secrets behind his own demise. As the annual summer festival approaches, Zorian must break free from the cycle before he becomes the main course again.
GameLit.

title: Jake's Magical Market
author: J.R. Mathews
description:
Jake scavenges for scraps in the ruins of his apartment market, until the world ends and an army of monsters invades - now he's on a quest to collect enough cards to build a deck that can take down the gods and save humanity. His survival depends on mastering the twisted game of apocalypse.
System Apocalypse / GameLit.

title: Spellmonger
author: Terry Mancour
description: Minalan stands amidst the ravaged streets of Boval, his adopted home under siege by an unrelenting horde of goblins - the Gurvani army has been marching for months, and their arrival means certain doom. The defenders are vastly outnumbered, with Minalan facing a desperate fight to endure the onslaught for even a day longer. GameLit.

title: The System Apocalypse Books 1-3
author: Tao Wong
description:
John emerged from the ruins of civilization, his eyes fixed on the blue notification boxes that signaled the end of the world - now a constant reminder of what was lost and what needed to be rebuilt. He set out to rebuild around the System, humanity's greatest enemy, with a mix of determination and dark humor.

Apocalypse Survival.

title: Ascend Online
author: Luke Chmilenko
description:
Here is a 2-sentence book blurb:

Marcus was tossed into a world that defied his wildest imagination, leaving him to navigate a desolate landscape and face marauding goblins in the remote village of Ravenshire. Now, he must rebuild the ruined village and help its survivors, all while trying to survive himself - Isekai.

title: Mage Errant: Publisher's Pack
author: John Bierce
description: Hugh of Emblin, a hapless cultivator and reluctant hero, found himself at the mercy of the labyrinthine underworld beneath Skyhold, forced to navigate pirates, monsters, and cultists with only his wit and sand-resistant magic to rely on. His survival depended on staying one step ahead of the conspirators hunting Indris Stormbreaker - Cultivation / System Apocalypse.

title: Domestication
author: Seth Ring
description: John Sutton, a former soldier, finds himself at the helm of a small farm on the outskirts of the empire, as the world burns around him - literally. His mission is to stem the rising Doom Points before they hit 100 and bring about the apocalypse, one burnt-out landscape at a time. System Apocalypse.

title: Iron Prince
author: Bryce O'Connor
description:
Reidon Ward trudged through the Galens Institute's halls, his stomach growling and his grades sinking faster than his already-low self-esteem. But when the school's most powerful AI, Echo, took notice of him, Reidon's desperation for acceptance and revenge sparked a fire that would drive him to climb the tower.

Tower Climb.

title: How to Defeat a Demon King in Ten Easy Steps
author: Andrew Rowe
description:
Yui Shaw, a down-on-her-luck mercenary, discovers that the world's 23-year-old Hero drought has become the most pressing problem of her life, as the Demon King's latest conquest threatens to snuff out humanity. With time running out, Yui sets out to fake being the Hero and find the legendary sword that might just save the world - for a price.

GameLit.

title: Ritualist
author: Dakota Krout
description: Joe's existence is a high-score death wish, constantly evading assassins in the game world where his abilities make him a lucrative target for the highest bidder. To escape the never-ending grind of survival, he'll master every skill and uncover the secrets of this twisted realm. GameLit.

title: The Perfect Run
author: Maxime J. Durand
description:
Ryan 'Quicksave' Romano careens through New Rome's chaotic streets, dodging corporate enforcers and cyber threats in a desperate bid to find his perfect ending - no matter how many loops he takes. With each failure, the city's darkness closes in, and Ryan's only hope is to try again.
GameLit.

title: Death, Loot & Vampires: A LitRPG Adventure
author: Benjamin Kerei
description: Vincent, a hapless gamer turned unwitting cult recruit, finds himself in the clutches of a vampire wannabe cult that's sucked him into another world to become their next soul-sucking pawn. To grow strong enough to rescue his family, he must master the dark arts and outwit these bloodthirsty posers - GameLit.

title: Super Powereds: Year 1
author: Drew Hayes
description: In a world where being a Super Hero and a regular human are mutually exclusive, our protagonist stumbles upon the dark secret to breaking this curse. With great power comes great humanity, but at what cost - their very existence? GameLit.

title: The Path of Ascension
author: C. Mantis
description: A lone figure awakens in the depths of an uncharted realm, driven by an ancient power coursing through their veins. As they strive to claim dominion over this untamed land, the very fabric of existence hangs in the balance, threatening catastrophic collapse. Progression Fantasy.

title: Unsouled
author: Will Wight
description:
Lindon's eyes snapped open to find himself in a world gone mad, where the strong devoured the weak and hope was just a distant memory. With nothing but his wits and an unyielding desire for survival, Lindon embarked on a journey that would either forge him into a legend or shatter his sanity.

Cultivation / System Apocalypse.
